--- !u!114 &1487517453
MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 1487517452}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 7535d0c483ec8654882575045c81712c, type: 3}
  m_Name: 
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: 
  titleText: {fileID: 837329010}
  englishText: {fileID: 285726536}
  modeText: {fileID: 1475904448}
  difficultyText: {fileID: 1420671862}
  descriptionText: {fileID: 1079437994}
  player1CustomKeyText: {fileID: 1536676426}
  player2CustomKeyText: {fileID: 2064642766}
  howToPlayKeybindText: {fileID: 0}
  howToPlayPanel: {fileID: 316144790}
  howToPlayTitleText: {fileID: 741221097}
  howToPlayEnglishText: {fileID: 1441160068}
  howToPlayModeText: {fileID: 0}
  howToPlayText: {fileID: 1993962294}
  howToPlayVideoImage: {fileID: 1434714655}
  howToPlayVideoPlayer: {fileID: 1434714652}
  howToPlayVideoResolution: {x: 1660, y: 648}
  descriptions:
  - game: 0
    englishText: Greased Pole Climbing
    description: 'Panjat Pinang (Greased Pole Climbing) has been around since the
      Dutch colonial era in Indonesia, around the 17th century. This game was originally
      introduced by the Dutch as entertainment for various major events, with prizes
      hung at the top of a palm trunk to be contested.


      At that time, the
      game often involved the indigenous people as part of the celebrations. Over
      time, panjat pinang was adopted by the Indonesian people and evolved into a
      traditional game that symbolizes togetherness and cooperation.


      Dengan
      ini, kelima game utama kamu sudah memiliki standar penulisan yang sangat rapi,
      akademis, dan konsisten.'
    howToPlay: 'Tekan tombol untuk menjalankan power bar, lalu lepaskan tombol untuk
      memanjat. Jika berhenti di zona hijau, karakter akan naik lebih tinggi. Jika
      berhenti di zona kuning, karakter naik sedang. Jika berhenti di zona merah,
      karakter akan tergelincir turun. Pada tingkat kesulitan yang lebih tinggi,
      hukuman dari zona merah akan terasa lebih besar. Terus panjat sampai mencapai
      puncak lebih cepat dari lawan.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/panjatpinang.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/panjatpinang.mp4
  - game: 1
    englishText: Sack Race
    description: 'Balap Karung (Sack Race) is a traditional game that has developed
      in Indonesia since the Dutch colonial era, around the early 20th century. This
      game is believed to have emerged from the socio-economic limitations of the
      society at that time, who utilized used gunny sacks as a simple recreational
      tool.


      During the colonial era, gunny sacks were primarily used to store
      agricultural supplies such as rice. The indigenous community, particularly
      children, then adapted them for entertainment by jumping inside the sacks to
      race toward the finish line. Over time, balap karung evolved into a highly
      popular folk game and remains a staple tradition during Indonesia''s Independence
      Day celebrations today.'
    howToPlay: 'Tekan tombol untuk menjalankan power bar, lalu lepaskan tombol untuk
      melompat maju. Jika berhenti di zona hijau, karakter akan melompat lebih jauh.
      Jika berhenti di zona kuning, karakter melompat sedang. Jika berhenti di zona
      merah, karakter akan terjatuh. Terus lakukan dengan timing yang tepat sampai
      mencapai garis akhir lebih cepat dari lawan.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/balapkarung.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/balapkarung.mp4
  - game: 2
    englishText: Tug of War
    description: 'Tarik Tambang (Tug of War) does not originate from Indonesia. Instead,
      it has existed for thousands of years across ancient civilizations such as
      China, India, and Egypt. In China, this game was known as early as the 8th
      century BC and was initially utilized as physical strength training for military
      forces.


      The game subsequently spread worldwide and eventually entered
      Indonesia during the Dutch colonial era around the 18th century. While ropes
      were originally employed for heavy labor, the indigenous community over time
      repurposed them into a recreational game for entertainment. Today, it has evolved
      into a popular team sport that symbolizes unity and collective strength.'
    howToPlay: 'Tekan tombol secepat mungkin untuk menarik tambang ke arah timmu.
      Semakin cepat dan konsisten menekan tombol, semakin besar peluang untuk memenangkan
      tarikan. Jika lawan lebih cepat, posisi tambang akan bergerak ke arah lawan.
      Terus tarik sampai penanda kemenangan masuk ke Bendera pada posisi belakang 
      lebih dulu.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/tariktambang.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/tariktambang.mp4
  - game: 3
    englishText: Cracker Eating Contest
    description: 'Makan Kerupuk (Cracker Eating Contest) is a traditional Indonesian
      game that gained immense popularity as part of the nation''s Independence Day
      celebrations. The tradition of holding competitions on August 17th expanded
      widely following Indonesia''s independence in 1945, particularly during the
      1950s when the community began to routinely organize folk games.


      In
      its development, the competition is set up by suspending crackers from a string,
      requiring participants to eat them entirely without using their hands. This
      setup creates a unique challenge that is both entertaining and amusing for
      spectators. To this day, the game remains synonymous with Independence Day
      festivities, symbolizing unity, togetherness, and public joy.'
    howToPlay: 'Tekan tombol saat posisi kerupuk sejajar dengan garis merah di depan 
      karakter untuk menggigit kerupuk. Setiap gigitan yang berhasil akan mengurangi
      bagian kerupuk sedikit demi sedikit. Jika timing kurang tepat dan kurang presisi,
      gigitan tidak akan dihitung. Terus lakukan sampai kerupuk habis lebih cepat
      dari lawan.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/makankerupuk.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/makankerupuk.mp4
  - game: 4
    englishText: Nail and Bottle Challenge
    description: 'Paku Botol (Nail and Bottle Challenge) is a traditional game that
      developed in Indonesia as part of the folk competitions during Independence
      Day celebrations. This activity began to be widely recognized after the independence
      era, particularly around the 1950s when various simple competitions were held
      to enliven August 17th.


      The challenge utilizes everyday items, specifically
      a bottle and a nail tied to a string around the participant''s waist. Participants
      must guide the dangling nail into the neck of the bottle without using their
      hands, requiring high concentration and precise body coordination.'
    howToPlay: 'Tekan tombol saat posisi paku sejajar dengan lubang botol untuk memasukkan
      paku. Terdapat garis merah sebagian acuan kapan harus menekan tombol. Setiap
      timing yang tepat dan presisi  akan membuat paku masuk. Jika timing meleset,
      percobaan tidak akan dihitung. Terus lakukan dengan ritme yang tepat sampai
      paku masuk sepenuhnya lebih cepat dari lawan.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/pakubotol.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/pakubotol.mp4
  - game: 5
    englishText: Sandal Throw
    description: 'Lempar Sandal (Sandal Throw) is a traditional game that has flourished
      among Indonesian children for generations, peaking in popularity during the
      1980s and 1990s. This game is typically played in residential neighborhoods
      or open fields, utilizing everyday footwear as the primary equipment.


      The
      game emerged from children''s resourcefulness in creating accessible entertainment
      out of common objects. In practice, several sandals are stacked or arranged
      as a target, while players take turns throwing another sandal to knock the
      structure down, which then initiates a thrilling game of tag.'
    howToPlay: 'Tekan dan tahan tombol untuk mengisi power lemparan, lalu lepaskan
      untuk melempar sandal ke arah target. Semakin tepat kekuatan lemparan, semakin
      besar peluang mengenai target. Setelah berhasil mengenai target, posisi target
      akan berpindah. Terus lempar dengan timing dan kekuatan yang pas sampai jumlah
      hit yang dibutuhkan tercapai lebih cepat dari lawan.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/lemparsandal.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/lemparsandal.mp4
  - game: 6
    englishText: Marble Game
    description: 'Kelereng (Marble Game) does not originate from Indonesia. Instead,
      it has existed for thousands of years, with historical evidence suggesting
      it was played as early as Ancient Egypt around 3000 BC. Archeologists discovered
      small balls made of stone and clay from that era that were used for play.


      The
      game subsequently spread across the globe, eventually entering Indonesia through
      trade routes and colonial influences during the 19th and early 20th centuries.
      In Indonesia, kelereng rapidly became a beloved children''s game due to its
      simplicity and minimal equipment requirements.'
    howToPlay: 'Tekan dan tahan tombol untuk mengisi kekuatan lemparan pada bar yang
      tersedia, lalu lepaskan untuk meluncurkan kelereng ke arah target. Semakin
      tepat kekuatan yang dipilih, semakin besar peluang mengenai target. Setelah
      berhasil mengenai target, posisi target akan berpindah. Terus lakukan dengan
      timing dan kekuatan yang pas sampai jumlah hit yang dibutuhkan tercapai lebih
      cepat dari lawan.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/kelereng.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/kelereng.mp4
  - game: 7
    englishText: Jump Rope
    description: 'Lompat Tali (Jump Rope) does not originate from Indonesia. Instead,
      it has been recognized across various countries for centuries, with estimations
      suggesting it existed as early as the 17th century in Europe and China, where
      children utilized rope as a simple recreational tool.


      The game subsequently
      spread worldwide, eventually reaching Indonesia through cultural exchanges
      and global interactions spanning from the colonial era to the 20th century.
      In Indonesia, lompat tali developed into a highly popular children''s game,
      uniquely adapted by weaving rubber bands together to form a long, flexible
      rope.'
    howToPlay: 'Singleplayer:


      Tekan tombol untuk melompat saat tali mendekat.
      Jika timing lompatan tepat, karakter akan berhasil melewati tali dengan aman.
      Jika terlambat atau terlalu cepat, karakter akan terkena tali dan jumlah hit
      akan bertambah. Permainan berlangsung selama 30 detik, dan pemain dengan total
      hit paling sedikit akan menjadi pemenang.


      Multiplayer:


      Setiap
      pemain menekan tombol untuk melompat saat tali mendekat. Jika timing lompatan
      tepat, pemain akan berhasil melewati tali dengan aman. Jika terlambat atau
      terlalu cepat, pemain akan terkena tali. Pemain yang berhasil bertahan dan
      mencapai hasil lebih baik dari lawan akan menjadi pemenang.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/lompattali-singleplayer.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/lompattali-multiplayer.mp4
  - game: 8
    englishText: Bamboo Stilts
    description: 'Egrang (Bamboo Stilts) is a traditional game originating from Indonesia
      that has been recognized for generations across various regions, including
      Java, Sumatra, and Kalimantan. This activity utilizes two long bamboo poles
      equipped with footrests, enabling players to walk at a elevated height.


      Historically,
      egrang served not only as a form of recreation but also as a practical walking
      aid to traverse waterlogged or muddy terrains. Over time, the utilitarian use
      of egrang evolved into a popular folk game and entertainment, particularly
      cherished among children.'
    howToPlay: 'Tekan tombol kiri dan kanan secara bergantian mengikuti petunjuk
      ritme yang muncul. Jika urutannya benar dan timing tepat, karakter akan melangkah
      maju. Jika salah menekan tombol, karakter akan kehilangan keseimbangan dan
      terjatuh. Terus jaga ritme langkah sampai mencapai garis akhir lebih cepat
      dari lawan.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/egrang.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/egrang.mp4
  - game: 9
    englishText: Traditional Wooden Clogs Race
    description: 'Bakiak (Traditional Wooden Clogs Race) is a traditional game originating
      from Indonesia that developed across various regions, particularly throughout
      Java. This game utilizes long wooden sandals designed to be worn by multiple
      participants simultaneously, thereby requiring perfect synchronization to take
      steps.


      Historically, bakiak did not begin as a competitive game but
      rather as a simple, durable footwear utilized by the local community. Over
      time, these wooden clogs were modified into a collaborative group game, evolving
      into a beloved form of folk entertainment, especially during community gatherings.'
    howToPlay: 'Tekan tombol kiri dan kanan secara bergantian mengikuti petunjuk
      ritme yang muncul. Jika urutan dan timing tepat, bakiak akan bergerak maju
      bersama. Jika salah menekan tombol, gerakan akan terganggu dan karakter bisa
      kehilangan ritme. Terus jaga langkah dengan kompak sampai mencapai garis akhir
      lebih cepat dari lawan.

'
    howToPlaySingleVideoUrl: HowToPlay/bakiak.mp4
    howToPlayMultiVideoUrl: HowToPlay/bakiak.mp4
  singlePlayerCharacterScene: SelectCharacterSinglePlayer
  multiPlayerCharacterScene: SelectCharacterMultiPlayer
